14/06/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- During visits to Croatia and Macedonia on Tuesday (13 June), Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayiip Erdogan praised the results of his talks with top officials in both countries in terms of both regional co-operation and EU accession. In Zagreb, Erdogan met with President Stipe Mesic regarding economic partnership and exchanging expertise in the Euro-Atlantic integration process. Later in the day, Erdogan travelled on to Skopje. Meeting with Macedonian counterpart Vlado Buckovski and President Branko Crvenkovski, Erdogan discussed ways to enhance bilateral trade and economic ties. (HRT, HINA, Makfax, A1 TV, TurkishPress.com - 13/06/06)
